# Git Commands Script - Correct Workflow

## Step 1: Navigate into the cloned repository
cd Uso-de-reposit-rio-de-artefatos-em-Gest-o

## Step 2: Check repository status
git status

## Step 3: Stage all changes
git add .

## Step 4: Commit your changes with a message
git commit -m "Your commit message here"

## Step 5: Push changes to GitHub
git push

## Alternative: If you need to set up git config first
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

## Troubleshooting
# If you get "not a git repository" error:
# - Make sure you are inside the Uso-de-reposit-rio-de-artefatos-em-Gest-o directory
# - Run: pwd (to see current directory)
# - Run: ls -la (to verify .git folder exists)

